The paper deals with planning for multi-robot coverage, specifically with unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs), which falls under the robotics (RO) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of kinodynamic path planning and goal assignment, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (AI) and control systems (SY) sub-categories. The paper also deals with resource allocation and optimization, which are topics in multi-agent systems (MA) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves simulation and real-world experiments, which are common in computer vision (CV) sub-category.
